article.headline: American U. 64, Colgate 58, OT
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Arvyda Eitutavicious scored 13 points Sunday, including the last two in regulation and four in overtime, to lead American University to a 64-58 victory over Colgate. American (12-13, 4-7 Patriot League) had four players in double figures as Derrick Mercer, Linas Lekavicious, and Andre Ingram contributed 13, 12, and 11 points, respectively. Colgate (9-15, 4-7) was paced by Jon Simon's 19 points. Kyle Chones chipped in 16 points and 7 rebounds and Kendall Chones scored 12 points and had 5 rebounds. The Raiders led the game 55-52 after a 3-point play by Kendall Chones with 3:47 left. American answered with 10 consecutive points, including 8-8 from the line, to lead 62-55 with 12.3 remaining. A three by Simon and two free throws by Mercer accounted for the final margin. The Eagles ended a three-game losing streak in and swept the season series with the Raiders.
